This general plan includes specific actions for a variety of personnel, from first responder to senior management. There is a list of names and telephone numbers in the ERP for key Ironhorse Complex personnel and emergency responders. The ERP, which was last revised in June 2010, is periodically reviewed and updated as conditions require. The overall emergency response program for the Ironhorse Complex is coordinated with the Uintah County Local Emergency Planning Committee (LEPC).
